cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI

The paper deals with detecting co-occurrence between events in multimedia event streams, which involves techniques from machine learning, information retrieval, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of finite state automata and processing algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
